stanford.androidlib

Class SimpleTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.os.AsyncTask<String,Integer,Void>
      • stanford.androidlib.SimpleTask

  • public final class SimpleTask
extends AsyncTask<String,Integer,Void>
    A simplified version of the AsyncTask class that does not require the use of generics or nested classes. A SimpleTask operates on a collection of string items. If you don't want to use strings, use the regular AsyncTask. 
     SimpleTask.with(this).execute(item1, item2, ..., itemN);

        public long getElapsedTime()

      • getEndTime

        public long getEndTime()
        Returns the MS time at which this task finished running, as a long integer of MS since the epoch (Jan 1 1970 12:00:00am). If the task has not yet finished running, returns -1.

      • getStartTime

        public long getStartTime()
        Returns the MS time at which this task began running, as a long integer of MS since the epoch (Jan 1 1970 12:00:00am). If the task has not yet been started, returns -1.
